 For GdCoIn$_5$ the best choice found for the experimental subtraction is YRhIn$_5$ while for GdRhIn$_5$ our calculations indicate that LaCoIn$_5$ should be used (see bottom panel of Fig. \ref{cv_todos}).
The entropy difference ($\Delta S=\int \Delta C_{vH}/T dT$) between the magnetic and non-magnetic compounds obtained integrating from zero up to the magnetic order temperature ($T_N=30K$ for GdCoIn$_5$ and $T_N=40K$ for GdRhIn$_5$) lies in the range $0.01 J/K\lesssim \vert\Delta S\vert \lesssim 1.9 J/K$ for GdCoIn$_5$, and in the range $0.3 J/K\lesssim \vert\Delta S\vert \lesssim 3.5 J/K$ for GdRhIn$_5$. This difference would lead, in the worst case, to an error of at least $\frac{\vert\Delta S\vert}{R Log(2J+1)} \sim10\%$ ($20\%$) for GdCoIn$_5$ (GdRhIn$_5$) in the magnetic entropy.

